<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Fans of The Masked Singer were furious that Kate Miller-Heidke didn't take out the top spot in the show's highly anticipated finale on Monday.</p>

<p>The 38-year-old singer, who was disguised as Queen, placed runner-up to Bushranger, who was revealed as actress and singer Bonnie Anderson. </p>

<p>And viewers were devastated that Kate missed out on the trophy, venting about her loss on Twitter.  </p>

<p>Missed out: Fans of The Masked Singer were furious that Kate Miller-Heidke didn't take out the top spot in the show's highly anticipated finale on Monday</p>

<p>'How on earth did Kate Miller-Heidke NOT win - she was sublime the whole way through,' tweeted one viewer.</p>

<p>'Kate Miller-Heidke should have won. She was incredible,' wrote one person, while another commented, 'Explain to me how Kate Miller-Heidke didn't win'.</p>

<p>Added another: 'Kate Miller-Heidke's performance was so glorious that it should've gotten her the trophy'. </p>

<p>Second place: The 38-year-old singer, who was disguised as Queen, placed runner-up to Bushranger, who was revealed as actress and singer Bonnie Anderson</p>

<p>Plenty to say: Viewers were devastated that Kate missed out on the trophy, venting about her loss on Twitter</p>

<p>Many fans claimed the talented singer was 'robbed' of the win. </p>

